To cite this set of shapefiles in publications use:

  Kouprianov, A. (2019). Marx.1905: Shapefiles of Russian Empire and Countries 
  of Eurasia based on Marx' 1905 folio World Atlas for the use with 
  historical datasets. 
  URL https://github.com/alexei-kouprianov/GIS.projects/tree/master/Marx.1905

A BibTeX entry for LaTeX users is:

@Manual{,
    title = {Marx.1905: A map of Russian Empire and Countries of Eurasia based on Marx' 1905 folio World Atlas for the use with historical datasets},
    author = {Kouprianov, Alexei},
    year = {2019},
    note = {ESRI Shapefiles},
    url = {https://github.com/alexei-kouprianov/GIS.projects/tree/master/Marx.1905},
  }

I have invested a considerable amount of time and effort in creating 
this free set of shapefiles, please cite it when using it for data 
analysis.
